You are what you disclose about yourself
On the occasion of its tenth anniversary, Google asserts that one can find them at the bottom of people's pockets the same way you find sky above their head. It knows where they have spent their vacation, which experts they consult and what their interests are.
This is still not enough, according to Eric Schmidt, who is one of the influential people in the organization.
While as to the sceptics establishing a parallel with Orwell's vision of horror, they do not properly see the essence of Web 2.0.
Eric Schmidt said, not long time ago, to the Financial Times that Google's main ambition is to gather even more information about its users. This is necessary so that Google's founders can keep to their original goal, which was as follows: "Let collect all the information in the world in a system!".
According to the executive of Google who was interviewed, after ten years of worldwide upheaval work, they are still only at the initial stage of their targets of being able to deal with all sources of information.
