Elites in danger.
The phenomenon had already been seen a few days ago, with the House of Representatives vote against the $700 billion rescue plan approved by the White House: a significant number of Americans were, and still are, more interested in punishing Wall Street than in saving the American economy.
And yesterday’s New York Times confirms it well announcing that the current crisis divides the Republican party, even more divided between his East Coast old soul, moderated, pro-federal institutions and pro-business community, and its new soul, on the contrary, conservative, hostile to « those of Washington » and to the world of finance, powerful especially in central and southern states.
The soul, precisely, which has made itself feel in a despotic way with the vote which I mentioned at the beginning.
However what has been mentioned is only one example of the changes, the big changes that the ongoing economic earthquake pre-announce or let already guess: not only in the United States, but everywhere in the West, and may be not just there.
In the United States as in Europe, the crisis seems to be accelerating phenomena hatching for some time, to the point where, in the new climate, they are solidifying and coming forth.
The first of these phenomena is the updating, the extraordinary stimulus, of the sovereign-state double category compared to a sort of renationalization of the economy.
The crisis, indeed, is a crisis of banking-financial institutions that have, obviously close relationships abroad, but who, above all, are involved on a large scale with the balance sheets of people and families who live in one country, in one state.
This immediately creates a political problem for those who govern it: i.e., how to respond to the difficulties and the protests of individuals and families who are not voters.
In short, the crisis appears economically worldwide, but politically, it is here nearly national.
The political internationalization really seems to be overtaked or, have little to say about that: the obvious evidence is provided by the European Union, which as usual, shared between the various interests and the various national strategies, not succeed to decide any common policy.
And so, it is from the government of each state that all are waiting for speeches, rescue and recovery plans, new rules, and especially a credits affection: when one’s going through a difficult period, only the States have the economic resources, the mass of financial resources able to try to put things back in place.
They also possess the necessary resources and the legitimacy to use them: two priceless resources, elements which no market or international organization can ever use in a similar way.
This new emphasis on the crisis of the nation-state is moreover in perfect harmony with the continuing major importance that the most recent economic developments of the economy tend to attribute to a factor somewhat related to this item: territoriality.
Indeed, paradoxically, when we were convinced to be entered from then in the Kingdom of the network, of the increasingly sophisticated technology, of the equipment failure, convinced that global finance was now intended to dominate world we realized just like that, that on the contrary our future will have to settle scores more and more with little material things such as water, harvest, oil.
Things that can certainly be transported from one place to another one on Earth, but which are definitively linked to a restricted area, a territory.
Thus, which is sovereign, has certainly more cards than that which is not, i.e., anyone who has the misfortune to live in a place without harvest, without oil and water.
I now come to the second novelty, however, which predicts a fracture.
He who says Territory, State, Government, inevitably says Politics, and thus Leadership.
Accordingly, the economic crisis seems to produce two converging phenomenae .
On one side, the awareness of the objective need for authoritarian leadership, the search for a person who will know how to take control of the situation.
On the other hand, a disrepute wave for the existing leaderships, economic species that have been proved inadequate and full of dark areas.
And furthermore, something even more profound, and in some sense, even worrying: a discredit, a suffering, an image of inadequacy, a sense of remoteness that tends to involve the entire class of leaders in a growing number of countries in the West.
Thus increases even more the conviction of the various classes, before the actions are the same ideas of the social elites until now to their apogee, their way of listening and of being, their culture in the complex acceptance of the term, to have same time, and to be increasingly more foreign with the opinions of the majorities.
In short, the demand for leadership is growing in a subterranean way, a powerful and multi-pronged movement of de-legitimizations of the ruling classes and the traditional political orders, which is being manifested in spontaneous electoral "revolts" and in the collective changes in mood very recently, from the conservative ascent in Bavarian Austria to the fall of the Labourites in Britain, to the rebellion of the American Congress against Bush (and it well may be that the victory of the right in Italy did not happen by chance).
We have the impression that the traditional elites, their parties, their programs, and also their rituals, their newspapers, their accredited intellectuals, their dimensions, one might say, still have more difficulty, which did not simply start today, in understanding and therefore explaining the deeper layers of Western societies and the fact that the economic crisis is magnifying, increasing and potentially creating a disturbance to an inordinate extent.
Seeing all this, to talk of a current "rebellion of the masses" on the agenda, seems frankly exaggerated.
But one says well, to keep one's eyes wide open, it is not without reason.
The super glue to walk on the walls.
Defeating the laws of gravity thanks to a super glue, and in the future, walk on walls like Spiderman.
This is the objective of various American research centers, and today, a team of four institutions has almost succeeded at it.
With an adhesive measuring barely 2.5 square centimetres, researchers have succeeded in keeping stuck a 100 kg body on a vertical wall.
Study- the American magazine Science has published the findings of some researchers from the University of Dayton, of Akron, the Georgia Institute of Technology and the Air Force Research Laboratory.
The material, invented by the team of researchers, is an evolution of those we know that use a particular structure of carbon, called nano tubes of carbon.
"The principle of the glue can be imagined as a series of tubes diperses as a pile of spaghetti." says Zhong Lin Wang of the Georgia Institute of Technology in Atlanta.
Scientists have been inspired by the legs of geckos, which are overlaid by microscopic hair which ensure the animal, a perfect adherence.
Tests performed on various materials, such as glass, Teflon, and sandpaper, have proved that the new adhesive is ten times more powerful than the legs of these reptiles, and also, that he "peels off easily from the walls," explains Liming Dai, researcher in the engineering faculty of University of Dayton.
Walk on the walls? – 'this material could be used as temporary scotch-tape" adds Liming Dai.
Maybe to walk on the walls as Spiderman? Maybe that yes, but researchers think of a use much less fascinating such as the connection between electronic appliances, given that the carbon nanotubes are conductors of heat and electric current.
Other applications could concern aerospace engineering.
For now, no super heroes.
Other Research - The University of Berkeley, in California, is doing it also, in the search for a new adhesive.
In an article in the Journal of the American Chemical Society,  California researchers introduced an adhesive made up of microfibers, like hairs, which clean dust off themselves during their movement over a surface to guarantee a perfect and constant grip.
Drugs: never with fruit juice.
caution on Pamplemousse juice, of orange and apple.
These drinks, consumed particularly in the summer because they are thirst-quenching and rich in vitamins, if combined with some vital medications, affect absorption, either amplifying or lessening their efficacy, with very serious possible consequences with respect to health.
David nailey, a professor at the University of Western Ontario in London, recalls the fruit juices risks, fresh or in can, if associated with certain medicines ingestion; during the 236th American Chemical Society national meeting underway in Philadelphia, he launches a new alarm: a glass of grapefruit, orange or apple juice is enough to reduce the some vital medicines absorption, canceling their beneficial effects and putting a risk on patients' health.
Grapefruit juice has already been heavily criticized because it is held responsible for increasing the effects of certain anti-arrythmics, antibiotics, tranquilizers, antihistamines and neurological medications up to toxic levels.
MEDICATIONS AT RISK - The Italian medications agency gave us this news in a newsletter dated two years ago, alerting doctors and patients not to underestimate the danger of this mix and to pay attention to what one drinks, if one is taking a medicine such as diazepam or methadone.
Not only grapefruit- according to experts, even orange and apple juice contains substances that inhibit medicines.
There is a long list of active ingredients whose effects are inhibited by grapefruit and other juices.
Hence, the calling of Michele Carruba, director of the department of pharmacology at the University of Milan: "These findings are in general, immediately reported to the various national and international agencies of medicines that should if needed, change the medecines informative notes.
One should always read the papers that illustrates medicines that one takes, and, if something is not clear, one shouldn't be impressed, but ask clearly to the doctor or the pharmacist "underlined the expert at the agency ANSA.
