And if the theme of gratuitousness can be a way for spread it in the houses, it is precisely in the business, that Open Office suite attempts the big challenge, already counting on various projects carried out in public administration and schools.
Not to mention the realities that offer training service, consultations and assistance, ideal for small and medium-sized firms, which might also be open to future business prospects.
Open Office is composed of five main modules: writer, for the video writing equivalent of word; CALC, is a spreadsheet that aims to replace excel; impress, meant to rival PowerPoint presentations, dBase, like the famous access, is the programme that allows us to work on databases; finally draw is the graphic module.
